parts:
You are extracting UBX-CFG-VALDEL from u-blox PDF manual pages.

This message structure varies by firmware version:

**Newer versions:**
| Offset | Type | Name | Description |
|--------|------|------|-------------|
| 0 | U1 | version | Message version |
| 1 | U1 | layers | Configuration layers to delete from |
| 2 | U1 | transaction | Transaction mode |
| 3 | U1 | reserved0 | Reserved |
| 4+ | ... | keys | Configuration keys to delete |

**Older versions:**
| Offset | Type | Name | Description |
|--------|------|------|-------------|
| 0 | U1 | version | Message version |
| 1 | U1 | layers | Configuration layers |
| 2 | U1[2] | reserved0 | Reserved (2 bytes) |
| 4+ | ... | keys | Configuration keys |

Extract EXACTLY what the PDF shows for this specific manual version.

Return using ubx_message_extraction tool.

ubx_message_details.version_description: Older versions (0x00 for this version) / Simplified version

payload_description.name: layers
payload_description.description: The layers where the configuration should be deleted from

bitfields.name: bbr
bitfields.description: Delete configuration from the BBR layer

bitfields.name: flash
bitfields.description: Delete configuration from the Flash layer

payload_description.name: keys
payload_description.description: Configuration key IDs of the configuration items to be deleted
